Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A working trip by Pavel Grachev, Russian minister of 
defense, to the troops of the Leningrad military district which 
was planned for today has been postponed, Yelena Agapova, the 
minister's spokeswoman, has told ITAR-TASS. She said that the 
decision to postpone Pavel Grachev's trip was made with a view 
to ensuring reliable control of the strategic nuclear forces 
while President Boris Yeltsin, supreme commander, and Mikhail 
Kolesnik, chief of the general staff, are not in Moscow. 

